This document aims to be a complete and up to date record of the analysis for vagueness 0, the pilot experiment.

The pilot experiment used subitizable numbers as well as bigger numbers. The instructions had the form: Choose the square with {{few, many},{two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine}} dots. The variables were: subitizability; vagueness; target_size; gap_size; side (i.e., which side was the bigger number on?)

Data

Get the data.

# make the data file from the individual subjects' data unless it's already there in the directory
if (!file.exists("data.txt")) {
  system("echo 'gap\ttarget\tside\tvagueness\tpair\tVersion\tLeft\tRight\tText\tCondition\tcorrectAnswer\tsubject\tactualAnswer\tisCorrect\trt' > data.txt")
  system("cat ../experimentCode/output/*.dat >> data.txt", wait=TRUE)
}

# read in the data from file
din <- read_delim("data.txt", delim="\t")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   gap = col_character(),
##   target = col_character(),
##   side = col_character(),
##   vagueness = col_character(),
##   pair = col_integer(),
##   Version = col_integer(),
##   Left = col_integer(),
##   Right = col_integer(),
##   Text = col_character(),
##   Condition = col_integer(),
##   correctAnswer = col_integer(),
##   subject = col_integer(),
##   actualAnswer = col_integer(),
##   isCorrect = col_integer(),
##   rt = col_integer()
## )
# make an R object copy of that original data file
original_data <- din

# add observation number for the whole data set
din$obs <- 1:nrow(din)

# add trial index for each subject
din$trial <- 0
for (s in unique(din$subject)){
  din[din$subject==s, "trial"] <- 1:nrow(subset(din,subject==s))
}
# make a df to carry forward
d <- tibble(
  obs = din$obs, 
  trial = din$trial, 
  subject = as.factor(din$subject), 
  item = factor(din$pair, label = c("2:4", "3:5", "6:8", "7:9", "2:6", "7:3", "8:4", "5:9")),
  gap = factor(din$gap, levels = c("BigGap", "SmallGap"), labels = c("Big Gap", "Small Gap")), 
  quan = factor(din$target, levels = c("BigTarget", "SmallTarget"), labels = c("Big Target", "Small Target")), 
  vag = factor(din$vagueness, levels = c("Precise", "Vague"), labels = c("Crisp", "Vague")), 
  subit = factor(ifelse(din$pair %in% c(1,2,5,6), "Subitizable", "Not subitizable")),
  side = factor(din$side), 
  text = factor(din$Text),
  err = 1 - din$isCorrect, 
  rt_ms = din$rt,
  rt_log = log( din$rt ),
  rt_reciprocal = -1/din$rt # rate of slowing: # We multiplied reciprocal scores [1/RT] by -1 [-1/RT] to maintain the direction of effects compatible for the three variants, effectively converting speed [number of responses per ms] into 'rate of slowing' - A linear mixed model analysis of masked repetition priming, Kliegl, Masson & Richter, VISUAL COGNITION,2010,18(5),655--681 (p.~662) 
)
## Warning in log(din$rt): NaNs produced
d$c.gap   <- ifelse(d$gap=="Big Gap", -.5, .5)
d$c.quan  <- ifelse(d$quan=="Big Target", -.5, .5)
d$c.vag   <- ifelse(d$vag=="Crisp", -.5, .5)
d$c.subit <- ifelse(d$subit=="Subitizable", -.5, .5)
d$c.side  <- ifelse(d$side=="Left", -.5, .5)

Size of the data is 1600 trials. There are 40 error trials. Error trials are removed from analysis of RT

d <- subset(d, err==0)

Select either trimmed or untrimmed data by comparing this plot with the untrimmed data. Also use this plot to choose the most normal data (logRT).

dat <- d %>% filter(rt_ms >= 0 & rt_ms <= 10000) 
dat %>% 
  gather(key=rt_metric, value=rt_value, rt_ms, rt_log, rt_reciprocal) %>%
  filter(rt_metric=="rt_log") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=trial, y=rt_value, col=vag)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se=F) +
  facet_wrap(~subject) +
  theme(aspect.ratio = 1, panel.background = element_rect(fill="white", colour="black", linetype = "solid"))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

dat %>% 
  gather(key=rt_metric, value=rt_value, rt_ms, rt_log, rt_reciprocal) %>%
  filter(rt_metric=="rt_log") %>%
  ggplot(aes(group=vag, y=rt_value)) +
  geom_boxplot(aes(x=item, col=vag))

RT modelling

Do a first lmer model. You can’t put subit or gap over items because they are between-items.

lmer1.ms  <- lmer(data=dat, rt_ms ~         vag + subit + quan + gap + side + (1|subject) + (1|item))
lmer1.log <- lmer(data=dat, rt_log ~        vag + subit + quan + gap + side + (1|subject) + (1|item))
lmer1.rcp <- lmer(data=dat, rt_reciprocal ~ vag + subit + quan + gap + side + (1|subject) + (1|item))

models <- 
rbind(
  cbind(tidy(lmer1.ms),model="ms"), 
  cbind(tidy(lmer1.log),model="log"), 
  cbind(tidy(lmer1.rcp),model="rcp")
)

lmer2.log <- lmer(data=dat, rt_log ~ vag * subit + quan + gap + side + (1+vag|subject) + (1+vag|item))
dwplot(lmer2.log %>% tidy() %>% filter(group=="fixed")) + 
  ggtitle("rt_log ~ vag * subit + quan + gap + side + (1+vag|subject) + (1+vag|item)")
